#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:3
msgid "What is MCDR?"
msgstr ""

#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:5
msgid ""
"MCDReforged (MCDR, hereinafter) is a tool which provides the management "
"ability of the Minecraft server using custom plugin system. It doesn't "
"need to modify or mod the original Minecraft server at all"
msgstr ""

#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:7
msgid ""
"From in-game calculator, player high-light, scoreboard manipulate, "
"structure file management to backup / rollback, you can control the whole"
" world by MCDR and its plugins"
msgstr ""

#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:9
msgid ""
"Greatly thanks to chino_desu and his MCDaemon 1.0 for the idea of such a "
"cool tool"
msgstr ""

#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:12
msgid "Advantage"
msgstr ""

#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:15
msgid "Vanilla!"
msgstr ""

#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:17
msgid ""
"MCDR runs above the server. It doesn't need to modify the server at all, "
"which keep everything **vanilla**"
msgstr ""

#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:20
msgid "Plugin System"
msgstr ""

#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:22
msgid ""
"MCDR has a hot-reloadable plugin system. You don't need to shut down the "
"server to update the plugins"
msgstr ""

#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:25
msgid "Compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:27
msgid ""
"We supports most popular server softwares (Vanilla, Fabric, Spigot, "
"Paper, etc.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:29
msgid "On multiple platforms (Windows, Linux, Mac, etc.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:32
msgid "How it works?"
msgstr ""

#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:34
msgid ""
"**TL;DR:** MCDR works like robot that stares at the server console, "
"respond to server output quickly, and inputting commands for users"
msgstr ""

#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:36
msgid ""
"MCDR uses `Popen "
"<https://docs.python.org/3/library/subprocess.html#subprocess.Popen>`__ "
"to start the server software as a sub-process, so it has the ability to "
"control the standard input / out stream of the server"
msgstr ""

#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:38
msgid ""
"Since the console output of a Minecraft server has a stable format and "
"contains a large amount of useful information about the server, e.g. "
"player chat messages, MCDR is able to parse and analyze the server "
"output, abstract them into different events and dispatch them towards "
"plugins for responding"
msgstr ""

#: ../quick_start/introduction.rst:40
msgid ""
"With the help of Minecraft command system, MCDR can send Minecraft "
"commands via the standard input stream to affect the actual Minecraft "
"server"
msgstr ""

